8 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 43-09-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is
9 amended and reenacted as follows:
10 43-09-02. State electrical board - Members - Terms of office - Vacancies.
11 The state electrical board must consist of fivesix members appointed by the governor for a
12 term of five years with their terms of office so arranged that one term and only one term expires
13 on June thirtieth of each year. One member of the board shall represent the public and may not
14 be directly associated with the electrical industry. The board must include a master electrician
15 who is a contractor, a journeyman electrician, a consumer member of a rural electric
16 cooperative, an elevator mechanic, and a person associated with an investor-owned utility. A
17 member of the board shall qualify by taking the oath of office required of civil officers and shall
18 hold office until that member's successor is appointed and qualified. The governor shall fill any
19 vacancy by appointment for the unexpired term of office.
20 SECTION 3. A new section to chapter 43-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
21 and enacted as follows:
22 Powers and duties of the board - Regulation of conveyances - Exceptions .
23 1. The board shall adopt rules to regulate the inspection and testing of conveyances and
24 to implement applicable standards published by the American society of mechanical
25 engineers. The board shall publish testing and inspection forms based on the rules
26 and standards adopted by the board.
27 2. The board shall establish procedures for monitoring compliance with this chapter and
28 receiving and investigating complaints.
29 3. The board may grant an exception or variance from the requirements of board rules if
30 the exception or variance will not jeopardize the public safety and welfare.
