1 4. The board shall hold hearings and hear appeals on disciplinary matters under
2 sections 4 through 10 of this Act .
3 5. The board shall establish fee schedules for permits, certificates, inspections, and
4 tests. The fees must reflect the actual costs and expenses to conduct the duties of the
5 board.
6 6. The rules adopted by the board may not apply to an elevator located in a single-family
7 private residence, a facility used for the purpose of energy generation, an industrial
8 conveyance the primary purpose of which is not the movement of individuals, or a
9 conveyance used in an agricultural facility.
10 SECTION 4. A new section to chapter 43-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
11 and enacted as follows:
12 Conveyance permit required.
13 1. a. Within six months from the effective date of this Act, the owner of a conveyance
14 shall register the conveyance with the board.
15 b. The owner of a new elevator or other conveyance must register the conveyance
16 with the board within thirty days after the conveyance has been inspected and
17 approved.
18 c. When registering a conveyance, the owner shall provide to the board the type of
19 the conveyance, the rated load, the number of landings and speed of the
20 conveyance, the name of the manufacturer of the conveyance, the location of the
21 conveyance, the purpose for which the conveyance is used, and any additional
22 information the board may require.
23 d. When a conveyance subject to this chapter is decommissioned or otherwise
24 taken out of service, the owner responsible for the equipment shall notify the
25 board within six months to request the conveyance be removed from the
26 registration list.
27 2. Before an installation or alteration may be commenced on a conveyance, an elevator
28 contractor shall apply to the board for a permit.
29 3. An application for a permit must include:
