10 conveyed.
11 f. A copy of the written maintenance control program for the conveyance.
12 4. The elevator contractor shall post the permit at the site of the conveyance while work
13 is in progress. The elevator contractor obtaining the permit shall be responsible for the
14 complete scope of work covered by the permit and ensure any alteration is performed
15 only by a licensed elevator mechanic and performed in accordance the requirements
16 of this chapter and any rules adopted by the board.
17 SECTION 5. A new section to chapter 43-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
18 and enacted as follows:
19 Conveyance permit revocation or suspension.
20 The board may revoke or suspend a permit upon a finding:
21 1. Of a false statement, omission, or misrepresentation of material fact in the permit
22 application or the plans or specifications on which the permit was based.
23 2. The work detailed under the permit has not been performed in accordance with the
24 application, plans, specifications, or conditions of the permit.
25 3. The elevator contractor failed or refused to comply with a stop work order from the
26 board.
27 4. The board determines revocation is necessary to ensure the proper enforcement of
28 this chapter or to protect public or worker safety.
29 SECTION 6. A new section to chapter 43-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
30 and enacted as follows:
