1 Conveyance permit expiration.
2 1. A permit is deemed expired if:
3 a. The work authorized by the permit is not commenced within six months after the
4 date on which the permit is issued or within a shorter period as specified on the
5 permit; or
6 b. After the work has commenced, the work is suspended or abandoned for sixty
7 days or a shorter time specified on the permit.
8 2. The board may allow an extension under subsection 1 .
9 SECTION 7. A new section to chapter 43-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
10 and enacted as follows:
11 Certificate of operation - Penalty.
12 1. Upon installation of a conveyance, an elevator contractor responsible for the work
13 shall certify compliance with this chapter, rules of the board, and any applicable
14 industry code or standard.
15 2. Before a conveyance is placed in operation, the owner of the conveyance shall obtain
16 a certificate of operation from the board. The board may impose a penalty of not less
17 than fifty dollars for the failure to obtain a certificate of operation.
18 3. A certificate of operation is valid for one year and must be renewed annually. The
19 owner of the conveyance shall pay the required fee before the board may issue a
20 certificate of operation and renewal of a certificate.
21 4. The owner of the conveyance shall clearly display the certificate on or in each
22 conveyance or in the machine room.
23 SECTION 8. A new section to chapter 43-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
24 and enacted as follows:
25 Reporting of accidents.
26 If an incident occurs involving an elevator or other conveyance which results in death or
27 bodily injury to any person which requires hospitalization or other treatment by a medical
28 professional, the owner of the conveyance shall submit to the board a report, on a form
29 prescribed by the board, within forty-eight hours. The report must include the date, time, and
30 place of accident.
