1 SECTION 9. A new section to chapter 43-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
2 and enacted as follows:
3 Inspection and testing of conveyances - Removal from service .
4 1. The owner of a conveyance shall ensure each conveyance is inspected and tested as
5 required by the board.
6 2. All work required for inspections and tests of conveyances must be performed by an
7 elevator mechanic and must be witnessed by an elevator inspector.
8 3. Upon completion of an inspection, the elevator inspector shall provide the owner of the
9 conveyance and the board a written inspection report verifying code compliance or
10 describing any code violations found. If a conveyance fails an inspection, the owner of
11 the conveyance shall remove the conveyance from service until the violations are
12 remedied to the satisfaction of the board.
13 4. The board shall develop a schedule for required testing and inspection of elevators
14 and conveyances in the state.
15 SECTION 10. A new section to chapter 43-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
16 and enacted as follows:
17 Elevator inspector and contractor registration.
18 1. An individual may not inspect any conveyance unless the individual is registered with
19 the board. An individual may apply for registration by completing an application form
20 provided by the board, submitting the application fee, and submitting documentation
21 demonstrating the applicant meets the requirements established by the board by rule.
22 2. A person may not perform, contract to perform, or advertise to perform alteration or
23 maintenance of conveyances unless that person is registered as an elevator
24 contractor with the board. A registered elevator contractor shall employ at least one
25 elevator mechanic.
26 3. The board shall create and maintain a list of all registered elevator contractors
27 operating in North Dakota.
28 SECTION 11. APPLICATION. The requirements of this Act must be phased in as follows:
29 1. After August 1, 2026, each newly installed or altered conveyance must pass an
30 acceptance test witnessed by an elevator inspector.
